The station’s first six-man crew would in fact be launched with it; the astronauts would ride in an Apollo-derived logistics spacecraft mounted atop the station hub. Upon reaching space station orbit, the astronauts would separate their logistics spacecraft from the station, move it away to a safe distance, and turn it so that they could observe station deployment.
